{#-
  Florida FCFDL / Fla. Stat. § 559.9613 — Commercial Financing Disclosure.

  Source-of-truth dossier: docs/compliance/03_florida.md, section
  "What § 559.9613 requires for disclosures" → "Required disclosure
  content (Fla. Stat. § 559.9613(2))".

  Florida is CONTENT-BASED, not form-prescribed. Unlike CA's 9-row
  § 914 table or NY's 10-row § 600.6 table, FL specifies the SIX
  required content items but does not mandate a row/column structure.
  This template uses a definition list rather than a table — semantic
  HTML that conveys the items, their values, and the regulator-
  prescribed framing without inventing a structure FL did not require.

  Notable absences vs CA/NY (the dossier explicitly enumerates these):
    * No APR row (FL does not require APR disclosure)
    * No average monthly cost calculation
    * No itemization-of-amount-financed attached document
    * No collateral requirements line
    * No anti-double-dipping disclosure (NY-only)
    * No prescribed table format
    * No broker-compensation written notice (NY-only)

  Required context variables:
    financer_name                     str — funder/lender name
    funds_provided                    str — formatted dollars; § 559.9613(2)(a)
    funds_disbursed_to_business       str — formatted dollars; § 559.9613(2)(b)
    funds_disbursed_lt_provided       bool — true when (b) < (a)
    deductions_explanation            str — short text describing why
                                            (b) is less than (a) (deductions,
                                            third-party payoffs, prior balance);
                                            empty string when funds_disbursed_lt_provided is False
    total_amount_business_must_pay    str — formatted dollars; § 559.9613(2)(c)
    total_dollar_cost                 str — formatted dollars = (c) − (a); § 559.9613(2)(d)
    payment_amounts_may_vary          bool — true → use first-payment estimate
    payment_manner                    str — e.g. "ACH debit", "split-funded credit
                                            card processor remittance"
    payment_frequency                 str — e.g. "each business day", "weekly"
    payment_amount_or_first_estimate  str — formatted dollars; either the fixed
                                            amount of each payment OR (when
                                            payment_amounts_may_vary is true) the
                                            estimate of the first payment per
                                            § 559.9613(2)(e) second clause
    has_prepayment_costs_or_discounts bool — true → describe prepayment terms
    prepayment_terms_text             str — short text describing prepayment
                                            costs or discounts; empty when none
    prepayment_contract_provision_ref str — reference to the contract section
                                            governing prepayment (e.g.
                                            "Section 7.3 of the Master
                                            Financing Agreement"); always
                                            required per § 559.9613(2)(f)
    rendered_at                       str — ISO date for the rendering
-#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>Commercial Financing Disclosure — Florida (FCFDL)</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: -apple-system, sans-serif; max-width: 760px; margin: 24px auto;
         color: #111; }
  h1   { font-size: 18px; }
  h2   { font-size: 13px; margin-top: 18px; }
  dl   { margin: 12px 0; }
  dt   { font-weight: 600; margin-top: 10px; font-size: 12px; }
  dd   { margin: 2px 0 0 16px; font-size: 12px; }
  .footer { margin-top: 16px; font-size: 11px; color: #333; }
  .meta   { font-size: 10px; color: #666; margin-top: 6px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Commercial Financing Disclosure</h1>
<p class="meta">Florida — Fla. Stat. § 559.9613. Provider: {{ financer_name }}.</p>

<dl>

  {#- Item 1 — § 559.9613(2)(a): total amount of funds provided. -#}
  <dt>Total amount of funds provided</dt>
  <dd>{{ funds_provided }}</dd>

  {#- Item 2 — § 559.9613(2)(b): total amount disbursed to business if less
      than item 1, with explanation of why. -#}
  <dt>Total amount of funds disbursed to your business</dt>
  <dd>{{ funds_disbursed_to_business }}
    {%- if funds_disbursed_lt_provided %}
    <br>{{ deductions_explanation }}
    {%- endif %}
  </dd>

  {#- Item 3 — § 559.9613(2)(c): total amount business must pay. -#}
  <dt>Total amount your business must pay to {{ financer_name }}</dt>
  <dd>{{ total_amount_business_must_pay }}</dd>

  {#- Item 4 — § 559.9613(2)(d): total dollar cost = item 3 − item 1. -#}
  <dt>Total dollar cost of this commercial financing</dt>
  <dd>{{ total_dollar_cost }}</dd>

  {#- Item 5 — § 559.9613(2)(e): manner, frequency, amount of each payment.
      If payment amounts may vary, the manner and frequency plus an
      estimate of the first payment. -#}
  <dt>Manner, frequency, and amount of payments</dt>
  <dd>
    Payments will be made by {{ payment_manner }}, {{ payment_frequency }}.
    {%- if payment_amounts_may_vary %}
    Payment amounts may vary. The estimated amount of the first payment is
    {{ payment_amount_or_first_estimate }}.
    {%- else %}
    The amount of each payment is {{ payment_amount_or_first_estimate }}.
    {%- endif %}
  </dd>

  {#- Item 6 — § 559.9613(2)(f): prepayment costs or discounts AND a
      reference to the contract provision creating the prepayment rights.
      The contract reference is required even when there are no costs
      or discounts (the merchant still has prepayment rights). -#}
  <dt>Prepayment</dt>
  <dd>
    {%- if has_prepayment_costs_or_discounts %}
    {{ prepayment_terms_text }}
    {%- else %}
    There are no costs or discounts associated with prepayment.
    {%- endif %}
    See {{ prepayment_contract_provision_ref }} of your financing agreement
    for the contractual provision governing prepayment.
  </dd>

</dl>

<p class="footer">This disclosure is provided pursuant to Fla. Stat. § 559.9613.</p>

<p class="meta">Generated by AEGIS on {{ rendered_at }}.</p>
</body>
</html>
